ital scan of <em>Rokhl M&#8217;vako al Boneho</em> was prepared by Aharon Varady from a copy held in the collection of the Klau Library (HUC) in Cincinnati, Ohio. The scan was made in order to create faithful transcriptons and translations with direct reference to the original work.</p>\n<p>A selection of 13 prayers appearing here were transcribed and translated by Rabbi Tracy Guren Klirs for her dissertation, later published as 转 转 <em>The Merit of Our Mothers: A Bilingual Anthology of Jewish Womens Prayers</em>, Cincinnati: Hebrew Union College Press, 1992. </p>\n<hr />\n<h3>Index of completed transcriptions and translations</h3>\n<p>转 撞注专 驻专 撞  转 爪 | <a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/prayers/praxes/mikvah/tkhine-when-woman-goes-to-immerse-mikve/\">Tkhine for when a Woman Goes to Immerse in the Mikve</a><br />\n 装撞旨注专 装住 旨 撞 砖装注专  爪 拽专   转  | <a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/prayers/life-cycle/living/child-care/women-who-have-bad-luck-with-children-should-recite-this-tkhine/\">Women who Have Bad Luck with Children Should Recite this Tkhine</a><br />\n 转 驻专   拽 驻 | <a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/prayers/life-cycle/jewish-life-cycle/marriage/tkhine-kaleh-before-the-khupa/\">A Tkhine for a Bride [to say] before the Khupe</a><br />\n转 驻专 注专 装住 驻专 拽  专 | <a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/prayers/life-cycle/living/learning/tkhine-mother-leading-child-to-kheyder/\">Tkhine for a Mother Leading their Child to Religious School</a><br />\n 转 驻专  注专 装住 驻专 专 拽 注 注专砖注   专 | <a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/prayers/life-cycle/living/learning/tkhine-mother-leading-child-first-time-to-school/\">Tkhine for a Mother Who Leads their Child for the First Time to Religious School</a>\n</div>\n",
